            Pholcidae
C.L. Koch, 1850 is one of the most species-rich spider families, with 1,946 extant species in 97 genera (

). 

Pholcus

Walckenaer, 1805 is the most diverse genus in the family, with 384 described species mainly distributed in the Afrotropical, Palaearctic, Indo-Malayan, and Australasian regions (

; 

; 

). The genus was split to 21 species groups by 

and 

